CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 4, 1967, pg. 12, reads: "Section 1 Champs - Shown above are members of the Schenley High Spartans who will be defending their City League basketball championship Friday against South Hills at the Civic Arena. Members of the Schenley team, shown following their title clinching victory against Fifth Avenue last Friday, are, left to right, back row, Kenny Durrett, Coach Willard Fisher, Montel Brundage, Roderick Horne and Robert Evans.  In front of Fisher is Edward Gibson.  Kneeling is Willie Clay, Seated is Henry Brandon. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School basketball players, back row from leftt: Kenny Durrett, Coach Willard Fisher, Montel Brundage, Roderick Horne, Robert Evans; Edward Gibson in front of Coach Fisher, Willie Clay kneeling, and Henry Brandon, with Tom Sumpter seated on left and teacher Leo Woods, posed in locker room with stenciled sign reading "Y SMOKE"
